sub_title: Coordination Centre of Foundation Dutch-Russian Livestock
summary:
The Foundation ‘Dutch-Russian Livestock’, founded at 11 September 2009, is a continuation of the Foundation ‘Development Russian Dairy Sector’, which was founded in 2005. 
The objective of the Foundation is improvement of opportunities on the Russian export market for their members. Besides, the Foundation will be a negotiating partner of the Agricultural Ministries of the Russian Federation and the Netherlands, on agriculture policy, looking after the interest of her members.

treasury_media.title: Annual End Year Meeting 2015
treasury_media.description: In the warm Christmas ambiance of the head office of CowHouse the Annual End Year meeting of the FDRL took place. On 11th December of 2015 together with our members, partners, friends and guests we have enjoyed an extended program, with inspiring speakers, interesting tour through the production facilities of our host CowHouse and at the end - a very surprising visit of the real Russian Ded Moroz, including nice Christmas presents!

projects.title: Companies on Tour 2014: Saratov-Ulyanovsk
projects.description:
Due to remaining interest to the companies of FDRL from the Russian authorities in these regions and on basis of information showing a great potential for the members the next Companies on Tour mission is organized to the regions Saratov and Ulyanovsk,
with full support from the governments of these regions and personal invitation from the Trade Representation of Russia in the Netherlands and Trade Economic section of Russian Embassy.
